# Phase 2 Verification and Flaws Resolution Plan

This plan documents the proposed fixes for all issues described in [billing-khata-flaws-report.md](file:///c:/MANAS/Projects/LK/Implementation/docs/billing-khata-flaws-report.md). The changes enforce strict database transactions on the backend and precise stock level validations and hook conformity on the frontend.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Transactional Database Operations**: We will introduce Postgres SQL RPC functions (`confirm_bill_transaction`, `cancel_bill_transaction`, and `log_repayment_transaction`) to execute checkout, cancel, and repayments atomically. This prevents race conditions and data inconsistencies.
> - **Strict Stock Checks (No Overselling)**: We will reject transactions on the database layer and block selections/increments on the frontend if a product does not have sufficient stock.
> - **Khata Requires Customer Account**: All Khata bills will validate that a valid `customer_id` is supplied, preventing credit bookings on unlinked profiles.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database Migrations

#### [NEW] [024_transactional_billing_and_repayment.sql](file:///c:/MANAS/Projects/LK/Implementation/migrations/024_transactional_billing_and_repayment.sql)
Add transactional database functions:
- `confirm_bill_transaction`: Creates bills, validates and decrements stock, inserts bill items, logs stock logs, creates khata entries, and increments customer total balance. Throws exception if stock is insufficient.
- `cancel_bill_transaction`: Reverses stock decrements and resets customer balances.
- `log_repayment_transaction`: Atomically inserts a repayment entry and decrements outstanding balance.

